Sounds like another asshat had to ruin it for everyone. Fortunately I didn't read the spoiler (on this torrent @ least), just everyone's admonitions towards him. With which I agree, of course, but as someone who reads through the comments for the SOLE purpose of ascertaining the A/V quality of the torrent, I really can't help wondering why they got rid of the +/- quality scoring system at the top. No offense to any of my fellow pirates, but the comments are almost completely useless in this regard. It's becoming just as common to find a spoiler in the comments as finding any meaningful appraisal of the A/V quality. And that's some bullshit. I'll never complain about getting stuff for free, but why would they get rid of something that only made TPB better and more useful? Surely I'm not the only one who used the Quality scores...am I??
TL;DR: Bring back the Quality +/- scoring system!!!
